What you need to know:

Among the 23 countries who have qualified for the Cup of Nations are defending champions Algeria, hosts Cameroon and record seven-time title-holders Egypt.Burkina Faso, Cape Verde, Comoros, Equatorial Guinea, Ethiopia, Gabon, Gambia, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Ivory Coast, Malawi, Mali, Mauritania, Morocco, Nigeria, Senegal, Sudan, Tunisia and Zimbabwe have also secured places.